[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: Determine manpage name from pod contents

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: 

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: This commit adds functionality to Pod::To::Man that allows it

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: to automatically determine the name of the generated manpage from the

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: contents of its pod. It does this by scanning the pod for

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: '=head1 NAME' or '=NAME' blocks and extracting the program name from

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: them. If it cannot determine the program name from the pod, it will

[10:18] <Geth> ¦ Pod-To-Man/main: default to the value of $*PROGRAM.basename.

